details.title: 95 Express Lanes to I-395 N Near Duke Street/Route 236
description: This is the last exit for all northbound Express Lanes traffic before the start of the I-395 HOV lanes.

At the end of the northbound Express Lanes, vehicles that do not meet the HOV requirement when the HOV rules are in effect will need to exit from the Express Lanes and reenter the regular I-395 lanes after Edsall Road. If the HOV restrictions are not in effect, all Express Lanes traffic can continue into the HOV lanes.
Learn more about the Express Lanes transition area.

details.title: I-395 N Near Duke Street/Route 236 to 95 Express Lanes
description: Vehicles traveling southbound in the HOV lanes will need an E-ZPass or E-ZPass Flex to continue into the 95 Express Lanes.
If you do not have an E-ZPass, or do not want to enter the Express Lanes, you can exit the southbound HOV lanes and reenter the regular I-395 lanes just north of Edsall Road.
Traveling on the regular lanes on I-395 south, your first opportunity to enter the 95 Express Lanes will be just before Edsall Road.
Learn more about the Express Lanes transition area.
